DATA COLLECTION PROCEDURES:
Subjects are recruited by the WiSo Laboratories of the Universität
Hamburg from the general student subject database by opt-in upon
invitation. No further restrictions are imposed. Subject payment
conforms to the standard rates of the WiSo Laboratories, which is
EUR 12 per hour on average, but the exact payment depends on the
decisions made during the study, as described in the section “study
design”. In the original study average earnings were USD 18.40
with an average duration of 70 minutes, which corresponds (at an
exchange rate of EUR 0.68 per USD on January 1st, 2008, the

middle of the original study period) to EUR 10.72 per hour at
current prices at that time. Adjusting for historical inflation in the
Euro area between 2008 and 2020 (approx. 17%), average earnings
in the original study amount to EUR 12.55 per hour at 2020 prices,
which is approximately equal to the hourly rate at the WiSo
Laboratories.
